## Editor features

When the `doc` tag is present, the [platformOS Check VS Code extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=platformOS.platformos-check-vscode) provides:

- **Hover documentation** — see parameter descriptions when hovering over a `{% raw %}{% render %}{% endraw %}` call
- **Code completion** — autocomplete parameter names at the call site
- **Parameter validation** — warnings for missing required parameters and unrecognized argument names
- **Type checking** — suggestions and warnings when literal values don't match the declared type

---

## Limitations

### Dynamic partial names

Validation is disabled when the partial name is a variable:

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% comment %}Validation disabled — dynamic name{% endcomment %}
{% assign partial = 'product/card' %}
{% render partial, title: product.title %}

{% comment %}Validation enabled — hardcoded name{% endcomment %}
{% render 'product/card', title: product.title %}
{% endraw %}
```

### Variable type checking

Type checking is only applied to literal values (`"string"`, `42`, `true`). Variables are not statically type-checked:

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% comment %}Not type-checked — price is a variable{% endcomment %}
{% render 'price', price: product.price %}

{% comment %}Type-checked — 100 is a literal number{% endcomment %}
{% render 'price', price: 100 %}
{% endraw %}
```

---

## Related platformOS Check rules

The following checks enforce correct usage of the `doc` tag:

| Check | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| [UniqueDocParamNames](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/unique-doc-param-names) | Each `@param` name must be unique within a `doc` block |
| [ValidDocParamTypes](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/valid-doc-param-types) | `@param` type annotations must be valid platformOS types |
| [UnusedDocParam](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/unused-doc-param) | Declared `@param` entries must be used in the partial body |
| [MissingRenderPartialArguments](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/missing-render-partial-arguments) | Required `@param` arguments must be provided at the call site |
| [UnrecognizedRenderPartialArguments](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/unrecognized-render-partial-arguments) | Arguments at the call site must match declared `@param` names |
| [ValidRenderPartialArgumentTypes](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/valid-render-partial-argument-types) | Argument types at the call site must match declared `@param` types |

